# Setlify Brand & Domain Guidelines

rule "brand-guidelines" {
  description = "Domain knowledge and terminology for consistent naming across Setlify"
  alwaysApply = true

  ## Product Identity

  - **App Name**: Setlify
  - **Tagline**: Simplify your worship planning
  - **Audience**: Worship teams, church musicians, worship leaders
  - **Context**: Users plan setlists for Sunday services and recurring worship events

  ## Domain Terminology

  ### Core Concepts

  | Concept         | User-Facing Term             | Description                                               | Avoid                                     |
  | --------------- | ---------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
  | Setlist         | **Setlist**                  | An ordered list of songs for a specific service/event     | "Playlist", "Set", "Song list"            |
  | Song            | **Song**                     | A song with metadata (title, artist, key, notes)          | "Track", "Item"                           |
  | Song collection | **Song Library**             | All songs belonging to the organization                   | "Catalog", "Database", "Repository"       |
  | Pinned songs    | **Quick Access Songs**       | Up to 3 frequently-used songs accessible from anywhere    | "One Touch Songs", "Favorites", "Starred" |
  | Team            | **Team** or **Organization** | A group that shares setlists and songs                    | "Workspace", "Account", "Group"           |
  | Documents       | **Files**                    | Sheet music, chord charts, lyrics, PDFs attached to songs | "Attachments", "Documents", "Assets"      |
  | Musical key     | **Key**                      | The musical key (G, C, D, etc.)                           | "Pitch", "Tone"                           |
  | Past keys       | **Key History**              | Record of keys used in previous setlists                  | "Play history", "Usage history"           |

  ### Secondary Concepts

  | Concept               | Term                         | Description                                   |
  | --------------------- | ---------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
  | Active use            | **Live session**             | Actively viewing files during a service       |
  | Event date            | **Service date** or **Date** | When the setlist is scheduled                 |
  | Invite link           | **Join code**                | Code to invite members to the team            |
  | Quick access position | **Slot**                     | One of the 3 positions for quick access songs |

  ## Quick Access Songs

  This feature lets users pin up to 3 go-to songs for instant access:
  
  - **Purpose**: Pull up frequently-used songs during spontaneous worship moments
  - **Location**: Floating button on setlist pages; configured in Settings
  - **Behavior**: Tapping opens the song's files directly
  - **Internal name**: `oneTouchSongs` (in code) â†’ **Quick Access Songs** (in UI)

  ## User Roles

  - **Worship leader**: Plans setlists, leads the team
  - **Team member**: Musicians who view and follow setlists

  ## Voice Guidelines

  - Supportive, not corporate
  - Brief and action-oriented
  - Use "you/your" (second person)
  - Verb-first for actions: "Add song", "Create setlist"
}
